#. <section class="sutta" id="sn14.33"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn14.33:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 14"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 14"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn14.33:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthavagga"
msgstr "4. The Fourth Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 33. Nocedaṃsutta → yo no cedaṃ (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn14.33:0.3"
msgid "33. Nocedaṃsutta"
msgstr "33. If There Was No"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.33:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn14.33:1.2"
msgid ""
"“No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā "
"pathavīdhātuyā sārajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, if there were no gratification in the earth element, sentient "
"beings wouldn’t love it."

msgctxt "sn14.33:1.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi pathavīdhātuyā assādo, tasmā sattā "
"pathavīdhātuyā sārajjanti."
msgstr ""
"But because there is gratification in the earth element, sentient beings do "
"love it."

msgctxt "sn14.33:1.4"
msgid ""
"No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā "
"pathavīdhātuyā nibbindeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the earth element had no drawback, sentient beings wouldn’t grow "
"disillusioned with it."

msgctxt "sn14.33:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi pathavīdhātuyā ādīnavo, tasmā sattā "
"pathavīdhātuyā nibbindanti."
msgstr ""
"But because the earth element has a drawback, sentient beings do grow "
"disillusioned with it."

msgctxt "sn14.33:1.6"
msgid ""
"No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā "
"pathavīdhātuyā nissareyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"If there were no escape from the earth element, sentient beings wouldn’t "
"escape from it."

msgctxt "sn14.33:1.7"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi pathavīdhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā "
"pathavīdhātuyā nissaranti."
msgstr ""
"But because there is an escape from the earth element, sentient beings do "
"escape from it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.173"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.33:2.1"
msgid "No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, āpodhātuyā assādo abhavissa … pe …"
msgstr "If there were no gratification in the water element …"

msgctxt "sn14.33:2.2"
msgid "no cedaṃ, bhikkhave, tejodhātuyā … pe …"
msgstr "If there were no gratification in the fire element …"

msgctxt "sn14.33:2.3"
msgid ""
"no cedaṃ, bhikkhave, vāyodhātuyā assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā vāyodhātuyā "
"sārajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr "If there were no gratification in the air element …"

msgctxt "sn14.33:2.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi vāyodhātuyā assādo, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā "
"sārajjanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn14.33:2.5"
msgid ""
"No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, vāyodhātuyā ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā "
"vāyodhātuyā nibbindeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn14.33:2.6"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi vāyodhātuyā ādīnavo, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā "
"nibbindanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn14.33:2.7"
msgid ""
"No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, vāyodhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā "
"vāyodhātuyā nissareyyuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn14.33:2.8"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi vāyodhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā "
"vāyodhātuyā nissaranti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.33:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañcime, bhikkhave, sattā imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ assādañca assādato "
"ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ na abbhaññaṃsu, "
"neva tāvime, bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaṃyuttā vippamuttā "
"vimariyādikatena cetasā vihariṃsu."
msgstr ""
"As long as sentient beings don’t truly understand these four elements’ "
"gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, they haven’t escaped "
"from this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its "
"ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—and they don’t live detached, "
"liberated, with a mind free of limits."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.33:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, sattā imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ assādañca assādato "
"ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññaṃsu, atha, "
"bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā "
"pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaṃyuttā vippamuttā vimariyādikatena cetasā "
"viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But when sentient beings truly understand these four elements’ "
"gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, they’ve escaped from "
"this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its "
"ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—and they live detached, "
"liberated, with a mind free of limits.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn14.33:4.2"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
